  "title": "Project Engineer/Senior Project Engineer (M&E - ACMV)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead and execute Mechanical &amp; Electrical (M&amp;E) projects, with a focus on <strong>Air-Conditioning and Mechanical Ventilation (ACMV)</strong> systems, from initiation to completion.</li>\n  <li>Ensure project objectives related to scope, schedule, budget, and quality are consistently achieved.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and liaise with consultants, main contractors, sub-contractors, suppliers, and internal teams to ensure smooth project execution.</li>\n  <li>Review and interpret project specifications, technical drawings, and engineering submissions.</li>\n  <li>Manage procurement schedules to ensure timely delivery of materials and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular site inspections to monitor work progress and enforce compliance with safety and regulatory standards.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and maintain accurate project documentation including progress reports, variation orders, testing and commissioning records.</li>\n  <li>Ensure full compliance with statutory requirements, building codes, and workplace safety and health regulations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>ITE, Diploma or Degree in Mechanical Engineering or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum <strong>3 years</strong> of relevant experience in the Singapore construction industry, preferably in M&amp;E and ACMV systems.</li>\n  <li>Strong technical knowledge of M&amp;E systems and local regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Excellent project coordination, communication, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and manage multiple project tasks effectively.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></p>",
